---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { CONTACT_EMAIL, SITE_NAME, SITE_URL } from '~/consts';
const lastUpdated = '2026-05-01';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description={`How ${SITE_NAME} handles your data: what stays on your device, what (little) we log on the server, and how third-party ads work.`}
>
  <article class="prose">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p><em>Last updated: {lastUpdated}</em></p>

    <p>
      This Privacy Policy describes how {SITE_NAME} (the "Service"), reachable
      at <a href={SITE_URL}>{SITE_URL}</a>, handles information when you visit
      or use the site. We have written this document in plain English, with
      additional notes for users in regulated regions at the end.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Data processed in your browser</h2>
    <p>
      The live preview tool on this site renders Mermaid diagrams entirely on
      your own device. The diagram source you paste into the editor is parsed
      and rendered by the bundled <a href="https://mermaid.js.org/" rel="nofollow noopener">Mermaid</a>
      JavaScript library inside your browser, and is
      <strong>not uploaded to our servers</strong>. You can verify this by
      opening your browser's developer tools and watching the Network tab
      while you type or click Render — no request containing your diagram is
      sent.
    </p>
    <p>
      The "Copy share URL" feature encodes your diagram into the URL fragment
      (the part after <code>#</code>). By web standards, the fragment is
      <strong>not</strong> sent to the server when the URL is requested,
      which means even our access logs do not see your diagram source.
    </p>
    <p>
      If a future feature requires sending the diagram to a server (for
      example, the server-side renderer described in our roadmap), that
      feature will ask for explicit consent before any upload happens.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Access logs we collect</h2>
    <p>Like almost every web server, ours writes brief access logs for the pages it serves. Each log line contains:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>IP address</li>
      <li>Timestamp</li>
      <li>Requested URL <strong>excluding</strong> the fragment, and HTTP method</li>
      <li>HTTP status code and response size</li>
      <li>User-Agent and Referer headers supplied by your browser</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      We use these logs for security monitoring (rate-limiting abusive
      traffic), debugging, and aggregate traffic statistics. Logs are rotated
      periodically and are not joined with the diagrams you type into the
      editor.
    </p>

    <h2>3. Cookies</h2>
    <p>The Service uses cookies and similar storage for these limited purposes:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Preference storage</strong> — we store your theme choice
        (light or dark) in <code>localStorage</code> on your device. This is
        not sent to any server.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Google AdSense cookies</strong> — once enabled, Google and
        its partners use cookies to serve ads based on your prior visits to
        this Service and other websites. See section&nbsp;4 below.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Analytics (optional)</strong> — we may run Google Analytics 4
        with IP anonymisation. If present, GA4 cookies identify a returning
        browser but do not see the diagrams you paste into the tool.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      You can disable or delete cookies in your browser settings at any time.
      Some preferences (such as dark mode) will simply reset.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Third-party advertising (Google AdSense)</h2>
    <p>
      This site participates in the Google AdSense program. Third-party
      vendors, including Google, may show ads on this site and may use
      cookies to serve ads based on your prior visits to this site or other
      websites. Google's use of advertising cookies enables it and its
      partners to serve ads to you based on your visit to our site and other
      sites on the Internet.
    </p>
    <p>
      You may opt out of personalised advertising by visiting
      <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" rel="nofollow noopener">Google Ads Settings</a>,
      or opt out of a third-party vendor's use of cookies for personalised
      advertising at
      <a href="https://www.aboutads.info/choices/" rel="nofollow noopener">aboutads.info/choices</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Contact form submissions</h2>
    <p>
      If you use the <a href="/contact/">contact form</a>, your submission is
      delivered via FormSubmit, which forwards your message to our email
      inbox. Your message, email address, and any other fields you fill in
      are handled by FormSubmit and by our email provider for as long as we
      retain the correspondence.
    </p>

    <h2>6. How long we keep data</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Server access logs: rotated and deleted within 60 days.</li>
      <li>Contact form emails: retained until we no longer need them to respond to your enquiry.</li>
      <li>Cookies and <code>localStorage</code>: controlled by your browser.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>7. If you are in the EU / UK (GDPR)</h2>
    <p>
      Under the GDPR, you have the right to access, correct, or erase
      personal data we hold about you, and to object to or restrict certain
      processing. Because the Service does not operate accounts and does not
      store your tool inputs, the data we realistically hold about a visitor
      is limited to access logs and any contact emails you have sent. You can
      exercise your rights by emailing
      <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>8. If you are in California (CCPA / CPRA)</h2>
    <p>
      California residents have the right to know what personal information a
      business collects and the right to request its deletion. The Service
      does not sell personal information. To make a request, email
      <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>9. If you are in Korea</h2>
    <p>
      This Service is operated from South Korea. To the extent the
      <em>Personal Information Protection Act</em> applies, we act as the
      controller of the limited personal information described above.
      Access, correction, and deletion requests can be submitted to
      <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>10. Children</h2>
    <p>
      The Service is intended for a general developer audience and is not
      directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal
      information from children.
    </p>

    <h2>11. Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this Privacy Policy as the Service evolves. The
      "Last updated" date at the top of this page reflects the most recent
      revision. Material changes will be noted at the top of the page.
    </p>

    <h2>12. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions about this policy can be sent to
      <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
